# Backend Rules

## Layering
- Keep controller thin: validate input, call service, map response.
- Put business rules in services, not in routes/controllers.
- Keep data-access logic in model/repository utilities, not in controllers.

## Validation and errors
- Validate all external input (params, query, body) before business logic.
- Return consistent error shape with machine-readable codes.
- Never swallow errors; log context and rethrow/forward to error middleware.

## Security
- Enforce auth and role checks at route boundary.
- Never trust client-calculated totals, discounts, or role fields.
- Do not expose secrets or internal stack traces in API responses.

## Data integrity
- Use transaction/atomic update for multi-step writes (order/payment/inventory).
- Make retry-sensitive operations idempotent.
- Store auditable status transitions for order and payment changes.

## Maintainability
- Keep functions small and deterministic where possible.
- Prefer explicit naming over clever abstractions.
- Add tests for business-critical flows (checkout, cancel, refund, stock sync).
